    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve factors met or exceeded required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) was accepted based on the regulatory mandate of ASTM F1717 as the single required test configuration and the supporting analytical argument that the compression-bending condition represents the worst-case loading scenario. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) were satisfied across all three FEA modeling teams. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission. Note: this package was submitted under ProfileMinimal with hash integrity protection; signature workflow is pending organizational PKI provisioning and will be appended prior to final archival.",
